</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Probably an adventive in the New World but may become established.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We have not seen 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. Carillo-F</emphasis>
557 but the shape and measurements of the sepals accompanying the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Infante-Betancour 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Infante-Betancour" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea austinii</emphasis>
(Infante-Betancour 2014)
</taxonomicName>
clearly indicate that it is 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. involucrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than the very similar 
<taxonomicName authority="Roxb. The" authorityName="Roxb. The" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. pileata</emphasis>
Roxb. The
</taxonomicName>
drawing of the inflorescence, however, is very stylised and difficult to interpret.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
••• The following four species are unplaced within 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We are unable to make even a guess at their likely placement.
</paragraph>
